qas.question: What does a power factor of 1 mean?

answers.text: the actual power consumed (in watts) and the apparent power (in volt-amperes) are equal

qas.question: What principally determines the wattage of an incandescent bulb?
What determines the resistance of the filament?

answers.text: the filament's length, thickness, and material

qas.question: How close do incandescent lamps come to pure resistive loads?

answers.text: Incandescent lamps are nearly pure resistive loads

qas.question: All other things being equal, how does wattage affect light emitted?

answers.text: the higher-powered bulb gives more light
